pageContext.claim: “I see these hearings where we have a great day. And then you pick up the phony New York Times, which is a total phony paper -- I don't read it anywhere, you can't read it. It's not even -- it has no relationship to the truth....Same thing with The Washington Post. It's a phony paper. We don't have it in the White House.”
pageContext.analysis: It's baloney when the president says he no longer reads The Washington Post or the New York Times. The White House apparently stopped getting print delivery, but Trump continues to refer to stories in both newspapers in public remarks and tweets.
